      <item>
        <title>Getting Started</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;!-- _includes/base.html --&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&quot;dependencies&quot;&gt;Dependencies&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CW&lt;/strong&gt; will currently only run on &lt;strong&gt;MAC OS X&lt;/strong&gt; or &lt;strong&gt;Linux&lt;/strong&gt; (i.e. &lt;strong&gt;POSIX&lt;/strong&gt;) systems. This means it is currently unavailable for users of &lt;strong&gt;Windows&lt;/strong&gt; Systems. This may change in the future.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://travis-ci.org/mjago/CW&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://travis-ci.org/mjago/CW.svg?branch=master&quot; alt=&quot;Build Status&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CW&lt;/strong&gt; is currently tested on &lt;strong&gt;Ruby&lt;/strong&gt; versions &lt;strong&gt;v1.9.3&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;v2.0.0&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;v2.2.3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&quot;install-ruby&quot;&gt;Install Ruby&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A fairly recent version of the Ruby programming language  (1.8.7 or later) is required to run &lt;strong&gt;CW&lt;/strong&gt;. See &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ruby-lang.org/en/downloads/&quot;&gt;Ruby Installation&lt;/a&gt; for details of downloading the latest version. To check Ruby has installed type the following to check the version:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;
ruby --version

&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&quot;install-cw-rubygem&quot;&gt;Install CW RubyGem&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://badge.fury.io/rb/cw&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://badge.fury.io/rb/cw.svg&quot; alt=&quot;Gem Version&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Enter the following commands to create the directory &lt;strong&gt;cw&lt;/strong&gt; (in the &lt;em&gt;home&lt;/em&gt; directory) - enter the directory - and install the &lt;strong&gt;CW gem&lt;/strong&gt; and its &lt;em&gt;dependencies&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;
mkdir ~/cw
&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;cd&lt;/span&gt; ~/cw
gem install cw

&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h4 id=&quot;how-to-run-the-examples&quot;&gt;How to Run the Examples:&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Download (or create) a test-script in the directory created. Run a test-script by typing ruby followed by the name of the &lt;em&gt;text file&lt;/em&gt; or &lt;em&gt;test-script&lt;/em&gt; that you wish to run:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;download: &lt;a href=&quot;../assets/rb/five-common-words.rb&quot;&gt;five-common-words.rb&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;
ruby five-common-words.rb

&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/tut/5commonwords.html&quot;&gt;Next - 5 Common Words&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
